        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "End of Course Performance",
          "Pass (1) vs Fail (0)",
          "3983 OULAD students, 649 Portuguese Students, 2000 Math students, 5820 Gazi University students, 7543 World University City Platform",
          "OULAD, Portuguese, Mathematics, 2 Classes in Gazi University in Ankara",
          "LMS logs, Student Characteristics",
          "[Dataset Dependent]",
          "End of Course",
          "Work takes as input a feature matrix. The feature matrix is processed via UDFmT, separating students and ccreating 7 uniform hypergraphs (constructed suing cosine similarity).\n\nThese hyypergraphs are then sent to a dual hypergraph learning module which is then directed to an attention-based layer. ",
          "SVM, Logistic Regression, SLFNN, GCN, MTGNN, FD-HGNNN",
          "Holdout Method (75/25)",
          "Dataset 1\n{Accuracy: 0.9111 - FD-HGNN (UniGAT)}\n\nDataset 2\n{Accuracy: 0.9234 - FD-HGNN (HGCN}\n\nDataset 1\n{Accuracy: 0.8858 - FD-HGNN (UniGAT)}}\n\nDataset 1\n{Accuracy: 0.8678 - FD-HGNN (UniGAT)}}",
          "The work by the authors invollves the creation of a novel neural network arquitecture meant to predict end of course performance.\n\nThe authors provide a mathematical description of the different elements:\n\n- Uniform Hyper-graph creation\n- Dual hypergraph learning module\n- Attention Layer\n\nAuthors show that the model outperforms all other tested models for the same task.\n\nAblation study shows that all elements of the network are relevant towards the prediction - first for elements. Then, the authors test different forms of Hypergraph formation and find UniGAT to be the “best one”.",
          "- Holdout method\n\n- Prone to over-smooth\n\n- No exploration of Temportal Dynamics"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
